cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.IR, cs.LG 

The paper involves the use of structure from motion (SfM) and deep learning on aerial imagery to estimate spatial distributions of rock traits, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) categories. The use of unpiloted aircraft systems (UAS) also suggests the possibility of robotics (cs.RO) being a relevant sub-category. The paper also involves the use of shape descriptors and semantic information extraction, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
